  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load architecture §6.4 + ADR-001 + ADR-008 + ADR-019.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `MemoryPromotionEndpoints.cs` (likely created by task 094); if absent, author it per task 094 pattern with the `MapPost` for `/reject`.</step>
    <step order="3">Map `POST /api/memory/promotions/{id}/reject`:
      - Endpoint filter: `RequireAuthorization` + tenant-scoping
      - Handler: inject `IMatterMemoryPromotionService`; call `RejectAsync(id, ct)`; map to 200 / 404 / 409.
    </step>
    <step order="4">If a `Program.cs` registration is needed for this endpoint group (and not already present from task 094), wire `app.MapMemoryPromotionEndpoints()`.</step>
    <step order="5">Author integration test at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Memory/MemoryPromotionRejectEndpointTests.cs`:
      - 200 happy path
      - 404 missing
      - 409 already-resolved
      - Cross-tenant → 404
      - Unauthorized → 401
    </step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Run grep across new endpoint code: `grep "AppendFactAsync" src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Memory/MemoryPromotionEndpoints.cs` must return ZERO matches (reject does NOT write to T3).</step>
    <step order="8">Measure BFF publish-size delta; write `notes/handoffs/095-bff-publish-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5).</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 095 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

